{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/bbc-sports-air-application-removes-its-offensive-language/","webpackCompilationHash":"ea08c84a4324927f2a47","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"James Ford","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"e1f16260-d825-5718-a4fa-e472dc9361e4","html":"<p>Well, that was fast (and rightly so).  This morning I posted about the <a href=\"http://www.psyked.co.uk/adobe/apollo/bbc-uses-air-to-install-a-list-of-swear-words-to-users-machines.htm\">BBC Sports' Olympics AIR Application containing a text file of offensive language</a> but now, roughly 1.5 hours after posting here, and 6.5 hours after it being initally posted, a new update has appeared for the Olympics AIR Application.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/48a11/bbc-fixed.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"bbc fixed\"\n        title=\"bbc fixed\"\n        src=\"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/48a11/bbc-fixed.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/afcd2/bbc-fixed.jpg 300w,\n/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/48a11/bbc-fixed.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The release notes mention that it's updating the listing events schedule (which it may well be) but it's also changing the contents of the <strong>bbc-swear.txt</strong> file to say '<strong>deprecated functionality</strong>'. (Instead of 1399 ways to swear.)</p>\n<p>Our experence is that the auto-updater appears a little buggy - clicking update seems to start a background download process, and the installer kicks in when the application is fully downloaded.  Unfortunately without a progress indicator, it seems that things just aren't working.  Nevertheless, a little patience and your application should launch the built in Adobe AIR installer soon enough.</p>\n<p>Fast (frantic?) work from the BBC!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"BBC Sports' AIR Application removes its offensive language","date":"August 05, 2008","tags":["air","auto-updating","bbc","olympics","swearing"],"url":null,"image":null,"description":null,"image_credit":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/bbc-uses-air-to-install-a-list-of-swear-words-to-users-machines/","tags":["bbc","olypmics","swearing"],"title":"BBC uses Adobe AIR to install a list of swear words to users machines.","date":"2008-08-05T09:01:35.000Z","description":null,"image":null}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/creating-outlook-calendar-events-through-http-links/","tags":["html","http-link","icalendar","outlook"],"title":"Creating Outlook Calendar events through hyperlinks","date":"2008-08-07T22:45:02.000Z","description":null,"image":null}}}}}